  },
  {
    employer: "Kentech",
    location: "Las Palmas de Gran Canaria, Las Palmas, Spain",
    position: "Backend Developer",
    from: "06/2017",
    to: "07/2018",
    description: [
      "I was hired as a Backend Developer due to my interest and performance in Node.js tasks during my internship. In the first six months, my main tasks were coding new features on Node.js microservices, helping the infrastructure area and handling deployments on our environments before CI/CD came to our lives. That meant handling web servers with Nginx and pm2 processes for Node.js, besides handling all the files on servers for other services.",
